4. Results
The analysis shows clear differences between conventional and green solvents:
•	Ethanol exhibits: 
o	Low XLogP → high polarity 
o	Good solubility in water 
o	Reduced environmental persistence 
o	Bio-based origin 
•	Benzene exhibits: 
o	High XLogP → low polarity 
o	Poor solubility 
o	Higher environmental persistence 
o	Known toxicity concerns 
These results indicate that ethanol is a more sustainable solvent compared to benzene.
_______________________________________
5. Discussion
The use of molecular descriptors enables rapid screening of solvent properties without experimental testing. Although simplified, this approach reflects early-stage decision-making processes used in chemical research and process design.
________________________________________
6. Conclusion
This project demonstrates that data-driven analysis can effectively support sustainable solvent selection. The results highlight the importance of replacing hazardous solvents with environmentally friendly alternatives and illustrate the role of computational tools in green chemistry.
